Expectations for a Successful Mentoring Relationship For a truly effective mentoring experience here are the expectations we establish with our mentees Communication Scheduling Stay Connected Please regularly check your emails and messages We send all virtual meeting invites via email Remember a webcam isn t required for our virtual sessions Punctuality Notifications Please be on time for our scheduled meetings We understand that life happens so if you can t make it please notify us immediately to cancel or reschedule Commitment to Attendance Consistent no shows disrupt the mentoring process After three consecutive no shows for scheduled appointments we will remove you as a mentee and recommend you seek a mentor through the Mentor Micro Center Platform Timeliness Please aim to be on time a maximum of 10 minutes late is acceptable Core Principles of Our Mentorship Trust Confidentiality Our relationship is built on trust I commit to providing a safe non judgmental space for you to share openly Non disclosure agreements NDAs are available upon request to ensure your peace of mind Clear Goals Expectations We ll work together to define clear realistic goals for our mentoring journey We ll also establish mutual expectations roles and responsibilities from the outset Active Listening Constructive Feedback I ll actively listen to your concerns and provide constructive actionable feedback In turn I ask that you be receptive to this feedback and willing to learn and adapt Accountability Follow Through We both play a part in your progress I ll hold you accountable for your goals and provide the necessary support and guidance to achieve them Your commitment to follow through on agreed upon actions is crucial Mutual Respect Empathy A successful mentoring relationship thrives on mutual respect and empathy We ll foster a healthy supportive environment built on these foundational values We re excited to partner with you on your journey to success
Project success nothing less

My primary expectation is that you are genuinely interested in giving yourself the best chance to succeed I have found in my own experience that there are no guarantees to success nor any foolproof formulas to making all your dreams come true Unless you re born into money with a huge network of powerful friends or family or you win some kind of lottery there is no other option but to do your best and be prepared to repeatedly pick yourself up off the floor every time you get knocked down And you will get knocked down many times If you have an amazing idea or product that nobody else is offering and will take the world by storm then you won t need a mentor to get you started Very few of us are ever likely to be in that situation so if you think you are then stop wasting your time talking about the idea and go out and make it a reality The other expectation I have is the need for you to be realistic in your own expectations Your ability to understand your own goals and the resources you have to help you get to where you want to go is crucial when it comes to mapping out a strategy and a path to the next step Some people strike it lucky but the great majority of us struggle to make it work Know what you re getting yourself into hope for the best but plan for the worst And never give up

I work with entrepreneurs that have AT LEAST ONE YEAR OR MORE of operation of a business and need help in analyzing how they can make the business sustainable and profitable We have once a month conversations in which we look at your current situation issues you are having and possible solutions for any problems Then I ask that you identify two or three actions you will work on during the following month In the next conversation we discuss your progress In the US Mexico and Canada we communicate via a phone call or Zoom In all other countries we communicate using WhatsApp Skype or other Internet based app You will need sufficient phone credits for each hour long monthly call IMPORTANT If you do not have AT LEAST ONE YEAR of operation of your enterprise please search for a mentor that specializes in working with starting businesses They can help you develop a business plan and cash flow budgets to help you get a good start Then after your first year of operation if you need assistance in planning for growing the business please contact me and we can discuss the possibility of a mentoring relationship Here are some resources for creating a Business Plan and a Two Year Cash Flow Budget for starting your business Business Plan Resources https www youtube com results search_query 22business plan 22 Cash Flow Budget Resources https www youtube com results search_query 22cash flow forecast 22 Here are resources for preparing an Income Expense Statement and Balance Sheet for your most recent year of production Income and Expense Statement https www youtube com results search_query 22business income expense statement 22 Balance Sheet https www youtube com results search_query 22business balance sheet 22

De una relación de mentoría exitosa espero una comunicación abierta honesta y constante donde pueda compartir ideas incluso aquellas que desafíen mis propias perspectivas La clave está en que el mentor sea adaptable capaz de personalizar su enfoque según mis necesidades específicas y de ofrecerme consejos prácticos y directos Lo que realmente valoro es que el mentor no solo comparta conocimientos teóricos sino que también me brinde oportunidades reales para aplicar lo aprendido ya sea mediante la participación en proyectos o facilitándome el acceso a redes profesionales relevantes Esa interacción práctica me permite poner a prueba mis habilidades recibir retroalimentación valiosa y expandir mis horizontes Para mí una mentoría exitosa es aquella que va más allá de las palabras es un proceso continuo de crecimiento y aprendizaje donde el mentor se convierte en un aliado estratégico que me apoya en cada paso de mi camino ayudándome a enfrentar los desafíos y avanzar en mis objetivos con confianza
